  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nMailservers are responsible for delivering historical messages. The app will automatically try to connect to different mailserver if it can't connect to current mailserver. But, user can navigate to Profile->Advanced->Mailserver settings and manually choose a mailserver he wants to use. After that, the app will always use the selected mailserver even if it is down. \r\n\r\nIt probably makes sense to somehow manually selected mailserver and infrom the user that the app won't try to automatically connect to other mailservers. The settings screen shows only currently used mailserver. But it does not indicate if the mailserver selection is locked because the server was selected manually:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/45292118-7e5f6100-b4f4-11e8-9742-05786f5ebfed.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nAlso, maybe \"Could not connect to mailserver\" snackbar should also mention that the apps is trying to connect only to one mailserver that was selected by user?\r\n \r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/45292263-f9287c00-b4f4-11e8-8c44-9acdd6928235.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.27\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
